Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.54,0:00:04.78,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}As times change,\Ndifficult cases will increase in number!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.78,0:00:07.05,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Shin'ichi's finally back today!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.05,0:00:09.02,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But something's not quite right!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.02,0:00:10.89,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.89,0:00:13.22,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.22,0:00:15.55,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.08,0:01:32.57,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A high school detective from Kansai, Heiji Hattori,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.57,0:01:35.79,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}suddenly appeared at the old man's office.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.79,0:01:39.22,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Seems he wants to challenge me, Shin'ichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.22,0:01:43.60,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Just then, a diplomat's wife showed up
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.60,0:01:46.87,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and asked for a background check of her son's girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.87,0:01:52.84,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}At her home, we found the diplomat poisoned to death in his study!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.84,0:01:56.17,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What's more, it was a locked room murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.17,0:02:00.48,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hattori finds evidence and figures out tricks,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.48,0:02:04.22,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}but my cold and the alcohol Hattori
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.22,0:02:07.42,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}gave me caused me to collapse!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.42,0:02:10.72,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But there's something not right about this fever!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.72,0:02:12.86,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Something's wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.86,0:02:13.89,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'm burning up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.89,0:02:16.19,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}My heart feels like it's gonna burst!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.19,0:02:17.86,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Well, Kudo?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.86,0:02:21.33,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If you got any problems with my theory, show yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.33,0:02:24.56,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Better hurry before I solve it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.91,0:02:33.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So who...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.53,0:02:36.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's the killer, Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.28,0:02:38.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not so fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.05,0:02:43.75,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What's the deal, Kudo? Forfeiting the match?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.02,0:02:46.06,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Fine by me...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.06,0:02:48.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.16,0:02:52.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd take at least 5 or 6 minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.50,0:02:54.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to kill the victim and pull off this trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.27,0:02:56.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The murder took place in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.10,0:03:00.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the 30 minutes between 3:30 and 4:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.34,0:03:02.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The doctor's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.91,0:03:05.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.34,0:03:07.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His wife is in the clear,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.21,0:03:10.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,as she was with us the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.15,0:03:13.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Similarly, the butler is in the clear,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.22,0:03:15.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,as he spoke with neighbors
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.15,0:03:19.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the whole time at the front door,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.09,0:03:21.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then greeted us all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.76,0:03:24.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, where are you, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.06,0:03:26.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The son and girlfriend are suspicious,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.60,0:03:32.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,since they arrived before the wife\Nand left when we arrived,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.24,0:03:35.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but they were gone for only a minute or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.07,0:03:36.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not enough time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.14,0:03:39.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} run off to?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.71,0:03:43.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.61,0:03:45.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which leaves just the old man
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.08,0:03:54.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,who arrived after 2:00 and watched TV in the next room over!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.73,0:03:57.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I found proof in the Japanese-style room...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.93,0:03:59.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the fishing line!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.16,0:04:04.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the latest and strongest type of fishing line!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.50,0:04:07.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a fisherman; don't pretend to play dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.51,0:04:13.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, on our way to this room, we ran into you at the stairs...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.58,0:04:16.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait in the Japanese-style room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.11,0:04:21.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, you were in the Japanese-style room after the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.99,0:04:27.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The fact this fishing line was in the garbage is immutable proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.09,0:04:28.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.33,0:04:30.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?! Am I wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.23,0:04:33.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, but has Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} been here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.87,0:04:35.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.03,0:04:38.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.10,0:04:42.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It was me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.07,0:04:44.41,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I win!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.41,0:04:49.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was the one who killed my son Isao—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.65,0:04:52.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope, I'm afraid not.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.08,0:04:53.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.69,0:05:01.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You got it all wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.63,0:05:03.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.09,0:05:05.60,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Shin'ichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.60,0:05:07.60,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Shin'ichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.60,0:05:12.00,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}So this is Kudo... Shin'ichi Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.00,0:05:17.48,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's... It's really Shin'ichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.48,0:05:19.34,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Shin'ichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.34,0:05:21.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where were you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.58,0:05:24.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You suddenly disappear and then reappear!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.55,0:05:26.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was... I was so worried!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.62,0:05:28.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit cryin, dummy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.85,0:05:29.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Gimme a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.89,0:05:31.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.89,0:05:34.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You show up now and say I'm wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.69,0:05:38.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you suggesting my theory is faulty?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.93,0:05:41.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.14,0:05:43.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.07,0:05:44.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're sweating...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.80,0:05:47.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be over soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.91,0:05:50.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shin'ichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.28,0:05:57.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with my theory, Kudo?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.45,0:06:01.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The trick you just explained is armchair theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.02,0:06:03.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's 100% impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.82,0:06:05.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Say what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.32,0:06:06.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.89,0:06:08.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to interrupt,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.86,0:06:11.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but his locked room trick works perfectly!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.50,0:06:14.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We even tested it out with my own pants!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.73,0:06:17.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You take a needle-ended line,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.37,0:06:21.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,tape the other end to the key holder,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.57,0:06:25.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and put the needle end through the pants pocket from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.58,0:06:31.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you pull both ends outside the room, lock the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.22,0:06:34.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and by pulling the needle end...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.72,0:06:40.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...the key will enter the pocket on its own!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.09,0:06:42.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,One last tug and the line breaks free of the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.89,0:06:47.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, by simply winding it up,\Nthe evidence disappears
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.97,0:06:50.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and creates a locked room!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.47,0:06:55.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is the key really in your pocket,\NInspector Megure?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.34,0:07:00.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the key was in a double pocket in the victim's pants...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.55,0:07:01.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.75,0:07:03.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.18,0:07:04.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you think we're lying, see for yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.68,0:07:07.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See?! It's in his double—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.39,0:07:13.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That... can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.29,0:07:17.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain I put the line through his double pocket!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.46,0:07:21.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was because Inspector Megure was sitting when you put the key in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.13,0:07:22.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.47,0:07:23.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he was sitting,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.87,0:07:27.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the pocket folded and blocked the key's path,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.07,0:07:32.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the tape came off before\Nit could get into the double pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.34,0:07:37.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus the victim was heavy-set, just like Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.08,0:07:38.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.88,0:07:41.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when I put my hand in the victim's pocket...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.95,0:07:45.86,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Damn, his pants are tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.86,0:07:50.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it could happen 1 in 10,000—\Nno, 1 in 10 times!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.43,0:07:53.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The result would always be the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.13,0:07:59.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Recall the key's direction when it was in the victim's double pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.54,0:08:01.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The key's direction?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.04,0:08:09.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Even if it did get in his double pocket 1 in 10,000 times,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.55,0:08:12.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it would only be the key holder.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.02,0:08:18.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The key couldn't possibly flip over to join the key holder in the pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.29,0:08:21.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The fact the key was fully inside
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.49,0:08:27.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,means the killer put it in the double pocket beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.40,0:08:31.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what about this needle-ended fishing line I found?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.67,0:08:38.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Another trap set by the killer\Nto place the blame on the old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.11,0:08:44.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I found a handful of others all throughout the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.18,0:08:47.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer planted them in other rooms, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.12,0:08:51.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So that it wouldn't matter where the old man was during the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.32,0:08:55.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But he admitted to the crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.29,0:08:59.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He simply stepped into the killer's trap, knowingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.90,0:09:03.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Though I don't know why.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.10,0:09:06.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This room was completely locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.17,0:09:09.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not suggesting it was suicide?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.27,0:09:11.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it wasn't suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.01,0:09:15.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus the killer's real trick is still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.88,0:09:17.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Real trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.08,0:09:18.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you forgotten?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.55,0:09:20.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When you discovered the victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.52,0:09:22.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,an opera was playing in the room
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.29,0:09:25.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and there were books stacked next to the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.16,0:09:28.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The opera was to drown out the victim's possible screams
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.09,0:09:31.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,after being poisoned with the needle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.23,0:09:36.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The books were to hide his possibly-contorted face.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.84,0:09:39.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.87,0:09:43.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whose eyes and ears needed to be fooled?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.11,0:09:46.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori... Yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.58,0:09:48.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.41,0:09:50.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not just you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.21,0:09:56.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,None of the others who came in with you noticed, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.15,0:09:58.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, you don't mean—!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.26,0:10:00.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When you entered the study,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.22,0:10:04.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the first one to approach the victim...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.53,0:10:12.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! The killer... was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.23,0:10:20.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! The killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.83,0:10:23.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was you, Madam!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.75,0:10:25.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She killed her husband?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.95,0:10:27.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.79,0:10:31.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean the victim was still alive then?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.56,0:10:37.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. She had only knocked him out with drugs or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.03,0:10:41.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then she poisoned him with the needle\Nwhen pretending to wake him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.00,0:10:44.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was only natural that no one noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.04,0:10:48.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If the sleeping drug and the poison were both powerful enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.44,0:10:52.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...the victim would die immediately after being pricked, as if asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.91,0:10:57.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She set up the opera and the books just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.92,0:11:02.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But if this sleeping drug turned up in an autopsy,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.25,0:11:03.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,this trick would've...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.15,0:11:05.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we wouldn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.26,0:11:08.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We assumed he was dead before we entered.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.83,0:11:14.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We only would've known he was knocked out before he was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.90,0:11:19.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, this was a psychological locked room murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.17,0:11:23.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,based on our assumption that\Nno one would ever invite a detective
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.67,0:11:26.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to a locked room and then kill someone in it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.41,0:11:28.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That what you wanna say, Kudo?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.05,0:11:29.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.55,0:11:32.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's see some proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.12,0:11:38.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, I didn't see her pull out a poisoned needle!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.36,0:11:42.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. She took out the needle
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.46,0:11:45.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,in a way that no one would notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.36,0:11:47.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Together with her key!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.10,0:11:48.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Her key?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.70,0:11:57.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Her key holder is of the same design as the victim's.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.21,0:12:01.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, hers should also split in two.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.15,0:12:02.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.58,0:12:07.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,please show us your key\Nand the inside of your key holder!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.15,0:12:10.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't mind, Madam...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.73,0:12:17.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What is this groove?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.30,0:12:20.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The poison needle was likely stored in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.97,0:12:26.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She customized it so she could pull it out right after entering the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.84,0:12:29.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, that very key holder
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.94,0:12:33.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,is definitive proof that she is the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.71,0:12:37.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why would she kill her husband?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.75,0:12:39.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If my hunch is correct,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.78,0:12:45.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,her motive is in this photograph.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.52,0:12:49.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is from when she was still young...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.06,0:12:51.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look closer, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.86,0:12:54.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't she look like someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.93,0:12:57.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She looks just like Yukiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.00,0:13:00.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's absurd!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.27,0:13:02.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See? Only her hair is a different color!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.97,0:13:04.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course she looks like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.91,0:13:09.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm... Yukiko's mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.18,0:13:10.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.01,0:13:11.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.38,0:13:13.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.62,0:13:16.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you had her with your husband, Isao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.35,0:13:21.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Yukiko is my daughter from my previous marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.19,0:13:25.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! She's the daughter of Kenji Yamashiro, a diplomat outcast
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.80,0:13:32.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,from society by my current husband Isao Tsujimura 20 years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.50,0:13:34.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenji Yamashiro?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.21,0:13:37.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the man who died in prison 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.71,0:13:41.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsujimura's goal was to get rid of him,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.45,0:13:43.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,since he was a rival diplomat!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.85,0:13:47.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then to obtain me as his wife!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.89,0:13:50.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband was arrested,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.62,0:13:53.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and Yukiko was adopted by his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.26,0:13:56.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Having hit rock bottom mentally, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.73,0:14:01.63,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I broke up with my wife just for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.63,0:14:04.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsujimura cajoled me,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.57,0:14:08.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and I wound up wife to that devilish man!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.21,0:14:15.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I realized it all when Takayoshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} brought home a photo of Yukiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.25,0:14:21.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At first, I thought it was just an uncanny resemblance, but Tsujimura...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.25,0:14:27.96,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Never! I refuse to let him be with the daughter of that man!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.96,0:14:30.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shocked, I continued to press him,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.90,0:14:36.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and he started to talk about how\Nhe framed Yamashiro for corruption.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.50,0:14:41.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And that his father had assisted with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.81,0:14:44.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.11,0:14:47.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't thinking straight back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.08,0:14:48.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.61,0:14:57.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You purposely took her bait\Nto try to make up for your past...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.99,0:15:01.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no use in pretending to be good, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.43,0:15:08.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he left this life as an innocent man who was framed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.57,0:15:13.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Takayoshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.00,0:15:15.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.01,0:15:19.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know I'm not fit to say this now,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.58,0:15:22.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but please take care of Yukiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.71,0:15:25.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.28,0:15:30.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah. So she was harsh with her daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.59,0:15:34.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so that she wouldn't realize.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.03,0:15:37.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hey, Kudo!\N- Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.56,0:15:38.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.23,0:15:40.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you OK, Shin'ichi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.56,0:15:43.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's just my cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.37,0:15:47.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But how'd you know all those details about the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.97,0:15:50.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You had to have been spying from nearby...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.57,0:15:55.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Get real. That kid with the glasses told me on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.48,0:15:56.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.67,0:15:57.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.85,0:16:02.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Said there was a weird detective from Osaka and to come right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.15,0:16:08.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-S-So I finished up the case\NI was on, hopped on a train—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.63,0:16:10.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.66,0:16:15.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He told me it's weird that you don't ask how I am on the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.90,0:16:18.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were actually nearby, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.37,0:16:22.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet you were watching\Nhow worried I was and laughing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.74,0:16:24.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now, Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.74,0:16:27.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you do that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.61,0:16:31.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm this... this...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.95,0:16:33.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't underestimate me, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.59,0:16:37.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.76,0:16:41.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell plenty just from your voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.49,0:16:47.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shin'ichi! Hold on! I'll go get the doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.70,0:16:54.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So my reasoning was wrong from the very start...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.17,0:16:57.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I lose in every which way this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.24,0:16:58.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're good, Kudo.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.94,0:17:01.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your logic's one level above mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.18,0:17:02.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.18,0:17:08.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no winning, losing, above, or below when it comes to logic...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.75,0:17:16.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all... there's always only one truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.93,0:17:21.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.60,0:17:26.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I was so focused on our match that I lost my cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.04,0:17:31.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kudo! Are you sure it's just a cold?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.48,0:17:33.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.61,0:17:35.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kudo! You alright?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.28,0:17:37.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.65,0:17:39.89,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}N-Not good...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.89,0:17:41.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.45,0:17:43.75,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}My heart again!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.49,0:17:49.39,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'm burning up!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.39,0:17:51.83,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's like my bones are melting!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.83,0:17:54.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.23,0:17:58.27,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Don't tell me I'm turning back...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.27,0:18:00.94,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}After I finally returned to normal!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.94,0:18:05.88,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Am I turning back into that kid...\Ninto Conan again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.08,0:18:08.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.91,0:18:09.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.65,0:18:12.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know you shouldn't be moving around!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.38,0:18:13.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're sick!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.92,0:18:17.56,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh no! If I turn into Conan now,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.56,0:18:20.05,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ran will discover my identity...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.26,0:18:24.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.57,0:18:31.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just his coat! Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.67,0:18:35.41,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Please! Don't make me turn back!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.41,0:18:36.61,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}At least let me tell Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.61,0:18:37.81,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.81,0:18:40.58,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}...with my real mouth
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.58,0:18:42.91,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and my real voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.91,0:18:47.41,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}...just one last thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.79,0:18:55.03,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Shin'ichi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.03,0:18:57.26,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}From in there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.40,0:19:00.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.47,0:19:06.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.61,0:19:10.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where were you?! I looked all over! And where'd you get that shirt?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.94,0:19:13.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I was all sweaty,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.38,0:19:15.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I borrowed this from that room...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.61,0:19:18.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, have you seen Shin'ichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.25,0:19:22.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shin'ichi-{\i1}niichan{\i0} said he remembered a new case and...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.95,0:19:23.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.62,0:19:26.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He changed clothes and went out the front door.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.59,0:19:27.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That jerk!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.66,0:19:37.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And he also said not to tell anyone he was involved with this case...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.90,0:19:42.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey! Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.21,0:19:44.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.60,0:21:20.80,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}After that, I was in bed for three days straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.80,0:21:23.57,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}During that time,\NHeiji Hattori went back to Osaka,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.57,0:21:26.48,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and thanks to my request to Ran right before I fainted,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.48,0:21:31.18,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Shin'ichi Kudo's name didn't appear in the papers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.18,0:21:38.28,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Now the men in black who shrunk me\Nwon't find out I'm alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.49,0:21:43.09,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But how did I turn back into my high school form?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.09,0:21:48.53,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait a minute! As I recall, he showed up, and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.53,0:21:53.30,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And then I drank that alcohol he brought!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.81,0:22:00.14,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.14,0:22:01.58,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's gotta be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.58,0:22:04.57,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I turned back by drinking that alcohol!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.68,0:22:08.22,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Alright! There's still a lot left!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.22,0:22:10.09,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}One drink caused that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.09,0:22:14.22,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If I drink this all, I can turn back completely!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.22,0:22:16.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.43,0:22:19.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you drinking, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.26,0:22:22.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I thought! Alcohol!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.67,0:22:28.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know kids aren't supposed to drink alcohol!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.31,0:22:31.11,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Don't be stupid! I'm a second-year high schooler!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.11,0:22:33.31,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait, that's still underage...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.31,0:22:35.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry and change your clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.10,0:22:36.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.21,0:22:38.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your friends are here!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.75,0:22:41.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.13,0:22:42.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.19,0:22:43.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.29,0:22:45.69,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Not you guys again...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.69,0:22:47.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We were so worried!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.62,0:22:50.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were sick for three days!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.39,0:22:53.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're so lucky you could skip school.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.46,0:22:54.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'll catch a cold, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.67,0:22:57.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll never catch a cold, Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.23,0:22:58.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.20,0:23:00.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like they say, "Stupid people don't catch—"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.97,0:23:04.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's good that you're back to normal now!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.07,0:23:08.58,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Man, I'm back to how I was...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.58,0:23:11.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So why do we have to go to the library now?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.52,0:23:17.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the only one who hasn't turned in a book report for class!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.42,0:23:21.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So we figured we'd help you out! Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.02,0:23:22.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yeah!\N- Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.69,0:23:28.50,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Whatever. Genta and Mitsuhiko are just sticking with Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-chan{\r\be10}...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.50,0:23:31.70,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But I guess I should go with 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.70,0:23:35.11,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Once I drink that alcohol and turn back into a high school student,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.11,0:23:42.10,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I might never get to hang out with them again...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.95,0:23:50.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, Tamada{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} has been missing since two nights ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.79,0:23:57.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-Idiot! Don't turn the lights on!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.57,0:24:08.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! I know where the body is hidden!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.41,0:24:14.66,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.66,0:24:19.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint: Backwards Book
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.95,0:24:21.70,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Is next time Conan's final case?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.13,0:24:24.59,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Detective Boys are indestructible!
